column2: In the graph \(G = (V, E)\) where $$V = \{a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i\}$$ and $$E = \{(d, g), (e, g), (d, i), (c, d), (e, f), (b, h), (e, i), (a, i), (g, i), (f, g), (a, c), (b, e), (d, h), (e, h), (d, f) \},$$ sort the following vertices in the descending order of their degree.
The degree of a vertex is the number of neighbors it has.
Drawing the graph can be helpful, but technically one could just go down the edge list and count.
